Japan's Daiwa Securities Co. Ltd. announced  Wednesday a pre-tax profit of 52 billion yen (505 million dollars) for the  year to March, reversing a loss of 7.27 billion yen a year earlier.
The country's second biggest securities company said operating revenue  rebounded 20 percent to 297 billion yen in the same period.
Daiwa forecast improved earnings of 60 billion yen in the current year  with sales increasing marginally to 300 billion yen.
